As of the [[2020 United States census]], there were 573 people, 265 households, and 179 families residing in the city.

===2000 census===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=January 31, 2008|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 642 people, 263 households, and 184 families residing in the city.  The population density was {{convert|96.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}.  There were 309 housing units at an average density of {{convert|46.6|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}.  The racial makeup of the city was 95.79% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 0.16% [[Race (United States Census)|Black]] or [[Race (United States Census)|African American]], 1.09% [[Race (United States Census)|Native American]], 0.47% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 2.49% from two or more races.  1.71% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.

There were 263 households, out of which 30.0% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 57.0% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 9.5% had a female householder with no husband present, and 30.0% were non-families. 26.6% of all households were made up of individuals, and 13.7% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 2.44 and the average family size was 2.96.

In the city, the population was spread out, with 24.5% under the age of 18, 7.9% from 18 to 24, 23.5% from 25 to 44, 23.5% from 45 to 64, and 20.6% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 42 years. For every 100 females, there were 98.1 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 90.9 males.

The median income for a household in the city was $22,313, and the median income for a family was $25,250. Males had a median income of $20,556 versus $20,385 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $10,778.  About 19.0% of families and 22.9% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 25.6% of those under age 18 and 20.5% of those age 65 or over.

